    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"638715\">Adomas Baliuka</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/113489-new-members/topic/.E2.9C.94.20How.20to.20formalize.20the.20following.20set.20proposition.20in.20lean/near/456778153\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I guess <code>X -&gt; Prop</code> will always be larger than <code>X</code> (if <code>X</code> is inhabited). (not sure if one can write a Lean proof of this)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This is Cantor's theorem, it is easy to prove:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Init</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Set</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Logic</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Function</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Defs</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Cantor</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">→</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"o\">):</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">¬</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Function</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Surjective</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">apply</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Not</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">intro</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">intro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h0</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">let</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">S</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">X</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∉</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">obtain</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">⟨</span><span class=\"n\">x0</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h1</span><span class=\"bp\">⟩</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">S</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h2</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">S</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">↔</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∉</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">h1</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h2</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h3</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∉</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">S</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h2</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">mp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h4</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∈</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">S</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h2</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">mpr</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h3</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">contradiction</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
